                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5041/7: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-01T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 1, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Your 12, January 27, 6 a.m. Department has been informed by Firestone that
                    labor bill was passed by Legislature January 29. However, the President
                    intimated on his return from Africa<note n="36" xml:id="d739fn36">For a report
                        on President Roosevelt’s visit to Liberia, see <ref target="#pg_658">p.
                            658</ref>.</note> that the subject had been broached to President
                    Barclay and a solution reached. Please report any information you may have.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
